it says: 

  • This enrollment process replaces the enrollment priorities normally used for other CS upper division courses, but  all members of your team will still be expected to be declared LSCS or EECS majors at least during phase 1 or phase 2 of Telebears.

does that mean you cant add the class, if you are still going to be undeclared in fall 2016?(so even after phase 2)
You need to add the CS169 Fall 16 class on Piazza for the link to work.
The Piazza link doesn't work for me! Where does it direct to?

Traditionally, enrollment in undergrad cs courses has been prioritized for cs undergrads with graduate students being enrolled later as possible.  I've sent the specific masters students who were listed as part of prospective teams to the grad advising team for them to advise me how to proceed.  In general, for masters students specifically, there is a concern that they will be able to have enough time to complete their graduate program in the one-year that they have.  We'll make these calls on a case by case basis after Michael Sun has had a chance to communicate with the specific students in question.

Does a student who is starting their CS Masters program count as "declared LSCS or EECS"? 

I wanted to confirm because it seems we have met all the requirements specified on the link, but our team has not been enrolled yet.

Thank you.

history.content:
A different enrollment process --which will require teams to be formed before students are enrolled from the waitlist-- for 169 will replace the enrollment priorities used for other CS upper division courses.    

See http://cs169.saas-class.org/fall2016

As of today (May 17, 2016), nine teams submitted requests to enroll but only three followed the clear instructions Prof Fox shared at the link above. Those three teams have been enrolled.  Others will need to have a team member resubmit if and when all members of the team are able and willing to do as Prof Fox asks.
